<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="315" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-21"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 21, 1864</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to inform your
                            lordship that Commander Rolando is supposed to be on his Way north, and
                            that when he arrives, inquiry will be made of him in regard to the
                            authenticity of the intercepted letter, a copy of which accompanied your
                            note of the 4th instant, respecting the case of the Sir William
                            Peel.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, my lord, your obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>